The linear relationship and AUC of indirubin standard solutions are calculated and is shown in Fig. 1
. Indirubin is identified using HPLC (280 nm UV) at retention time of 31.560 minutes and purification factor of 998.594 (Fig. 2
). The results from our research indicate that the amounts of the three analytes of IR extract powder are 4.2±0.1 μg/g.

A significant decline in granulocyte, monocyte, and lymphocyte counts are observed in the sham compared with the naive group (p<0.001, Table 2
). Immunosuppressant effect of irradiation is evident in this animal model. Significantly increased lymphocyte, monocyte and granulocyte counts are observed in the IR-M and IR-H groups when compared to the irradiated controls. L-glutamine group also exhibited similar effects but the degree of effect is less compared with the IR groups. These enhancements of hematopoiesis effects are due to the increased serum G-CSF concentration in IR treated groups (p<0.05, Fig. 3
).

Significant reduction in the height and number of villi is observed in the radiation groups compared with the sham and the naive group by hematoxylin and eosin stain (Table 3
and Fig. 7
). These results suggest that jejunum villi are destroyed by irradiation and this intestine toxicity model in mice is effective. IR-H group significantly shows an increase in villi number but not villi height when compared with the sham (p<0.01). The same radioprotective effect is also found in the L-glutamine group (p<0.01).
